      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HES CHARLIES ANGEL (5) resumes after finishing tenth at his latest appearance at Penrith on May 7. Finds a suitable assignment and will take plenty of beating. KING SAINT (6) produced a better effort at his latest appearance when second over 1720m at Melton, beaten 3 metres after coming from a long way back. This looks a sterner test than last time but he is capable of another big performance. ROLLONART (4) is a great chance after a string of sound recent performances, the latest a solid third at Riverina Paceway over 2270m. Hard to find fault. MICHEN ROY (8) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished seventh last start over 2240m at Melton, coming home 6 metres from the winner. No harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon. This doesn't look as hard so he is capable of turning things around.",
